card.name: Secret Rendezvous
card.oracle_text: You and target opponent each draw three cards.
card.flavor_text: Strixhaven's five colleges encourage natural rivalries among the students, but some bonds transcend all barriers.

Silverquill Campus enters tapped.
{T}: Add {W} or {B}.
{4}, {T}: Scry 1.
card.flavor_text: Mage-students drawn to the power of language choose Silverquill, the college of eloquence.

card.name: Fracture
card.oracle_text: Destroy target artifact, enchantment, or planeswalker.
card.flavor_text:
"Your defiance is amusing, little mage. It's time you learn how fragile you really are."
—Extus Narr

card.name: Study Hall
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}, {T}: Add one mana of any color. When you spend this mana to cast your commander, scry X, where X is the number of times it's been cast from the command zone this game.

card.name: Arcane Signet
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text: It started as a mere drop of water. The Magic Mirror crystallized it into much more.

card.name: Mind Stone
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {C}.
{1}, {T}, Sacrifice Mind Stone: Draw a card.
card.flavor_text:
"What is mana but possibility, an idea not yet given form?"
—Jhoira, master artificer

card.name: Sol Ring
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text: Lost to time is the artificer's art of trapping light from a distant star in a ring of purest gold.

card.name: Inkshield
card.oracle_text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt to you this turn. For each 1 damage prevented this way, create a 2/1 white and black Inkling creature token with flying.
card.flavor_text: Silverquill's elite know how to offer a scathing rebuttal without uttering a word.

card.name: Tempting Contract
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of your upkeep, each opponent may create a Treasure token. For each opponent who does, you create a Treasure token.
card.flavor_text:
"Don't think of it as debt. Think of it as an investment in yourself."
—Diriga, demon bursar

card.oracle_text: You draw X cards and you lose X life, where X is the mana value of a commander you own on the battlefield or in the command zone.
card.flavor_text: Silverquill first-years welcome discomfort in the classroom, knowing it will prepare them for the years ahead.

card.oracle_text:
{T}, Sacrifice a creature: Put two +1/+1 counters on target creature.
{T}, Remove a counter from a creature you control: Create a Treasure token.
{T}, Sacrifice an artifact: Create a 2/1 white and black Inkling creature token with flying.

card.name: Incarnation Technique
card.oracle_text:
Demonstrate (When you cast this spell, you may copy it. If you do, choose an opponent to also copy it.)
Mill five cards, then return a creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
card.flavor_text: "Draw out your fear, but don't let it control you. You're in charge now."

card.name: Cunning Rhetoric
card.oracle_text: Whenever an opponent attacks you and/or one or more planeswalkers you control, exile the top card of that player's library. You may play that card for as long as it remains exiled, and you may spend mana as though it were mana of any color to cast it.

card.name: Keen Duelist
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you and target opponent each reveal the top card of your library. You each lose life equal to the mana value of the card revealed by the other player. You each put the card you revealed into your hand.

card.name: Bold Plagiarist
card.oracle_text:
Flash
Whenever an opponent puts one or more counters on a creature they control, they put the same number and kind of counters on Bold Plagiarist.
card.flavor_text: "I know a good idea when I see one."

card.oracle_text: When Author of Shadows enters, exile all opponents' graveyards. Choose a nonland card exiled this way. You may cast that card for as long as it remains exiled, and you may spend mana as though it were mana of any color to cast that spell.

card.name: Scholarship Sponsor
card.oracle_text: When Scholarship Sponsor enters, each player who controls fewer lands than the player who controls the most lands searches their library for a number of basic land cards less than or equal to the difference, puts those cards onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffles.

card.name: Nils, Discipline Enforcer
card.oracle_text:
At the beginning of your end step, for each player, put a +1/+1 counter on up to one target creature that player controls.
Each creature with one or more counters on it can't attack you or planeswalkers you control unless its controller pays {X}, where X is the number of counters on that creature.

card.oracle_text:
Flying

card.flavor_text: "It's us against the world. Forever."

card.oracle_text:
Flying

({W/B} can be paid with either {W} or {B}.)
At the beginning of your upkeep, put target creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control.

+1: Put a loyalty counter on Gideon, Champion of Justice for each creature target opponent controls.
0: Until end of turn, Gideon, Champion of Justice becomes a Human Soldier creature with power and toughness each equal to the number of loyalty counters on him and gains indestructible. He's still a planeswalker. Prevent all damage that would be dealt to him this turn.
−15: Exile all other permanents.

Choose an opponent. You and that player each sacrifice a creature. Each player who sacrificed a creature this way draws two cards.

Flying

Flying

If grace gets more votes, each player returns each creature card from their graveyard to the battlefield. If condemnation gets more votes or the vote is tied, destroy all creatures other than Magister of Worth.
